databricks-sdk-cpp provides CMake targets:

  find_package(databricks_sdk CONFIG REQUIRED)
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE databricks_sdk::databricks_sdk)

Note: This library requires ODBC to be available on the system:
  - Windows: Built-in ODBC Driver Manager
  - Linux/macOS: Install unixODBC (e.g., `brew install unixodbc` or `apt install unixodbc-dev`)

Additionally, you need the Simba Spark ODBC Driver installed:
  Download from: https://www.databricks.com/spark/odbc-drivers-download

For configuration, see: https://github.com/calvinjmin/databricks-sdk-cpp#configuration

